# Retros — {{project_name}}

One entry per `/retro` cycle. Reverse chronological (newest at top).

## Per-entry format

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — week N retro

### What shipped
- (concrete user-visible outcomes, not commits)

### What surprised me
- (anything that took longer / shorter / went sideways vs. expected)

### Mistakes I made twice
- (promote to KNOWN_GOTCHAS.md if recurring 3+ times)

### Workflow changes for next week
- (concrete process tweaks)

### Stats (optional)
- Bugs caught by verification gate: N
- Correction loops avoided: N
- /context-save runs: N
```

## How retros land here

Run `/retro` at the end of a focused work block (end of day, end of sprint).
The skill drafts the entry from your commit history + your input, you approve,
it appends to this file.

